br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: re:</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Your parents spent 2-4 mos every year on strike? So what does that tell you about the company they worked for? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Nothing really.  Contracts were typically 2 years, so there's the biennial strike over the contract because the Teamsters couldn't settle a contract about wiping their ass without going on a &quot;We won't @#%$ until we get Charmin&quot; strike.  Hell, in the town I lived in, United Auto Workers went on a 9 month strike because the company wouldn't give people a paid holiday on their birthday.  9 @#%$ months because people were too lazy to use a vacation day on their birthday like the rest of the world, and they wanted to be able to show up late on shift without being docked (I'm completely serious here).  That little bit of mental wizardry meant, for example, that truck drivers like my parents were out of work.  So, because a bunch of lazy arses in a General Motors plant wanted their birthdays off and the ability to not be punctual, I had to eat Kraft Macaroni and cheese for 6 months because it was all we could afford.<br>
<br>
The &quot;off&quot; years were typically &quot;supporting the brotherhood&quot; strikes where the United Pud Pullers of America or some similar bunch of yahoos would go on strike in a related industry and the Teamsters would pull a strike to show their support.<br>
<br>
Night shift in the car plants near where my family grew up are a joke.  Union nimrods show up to work on night shift with sleeping bags because you can't fire their sorry arses out the door.  Next time you buy a North American made car, think about the fact that there's a 33% chance it was at least partially assembled by a jackass who showed up late for work and slept through his shift instead of making sure your car was assembled properly, all for $35 or more an hour...  And when your seat belt detaches in an accident and your skull is flying like an enraged coconut through the windshield, you can sing &quot;Look for the Union Label!&quot; while you wait for the ambulance. <p><center><img src=http://www3.sympatico.ca/pdcowan/qrgsig.jpg alt="Qrg at play"></center></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#628CBC>- </font><a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards>Morell-Thule Forums</a><font color=#628CBC> - </font><a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5>Off Topic</a> <font color=#628CBC> - </font><a href="http://sevendragons.net">Morell-Thule Community Website</a><font color=#628CBC> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.9.5.3<br>Copyright ©1999-2002 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

